Q. using the agr perform the following task
1. select students whose marks>=80 
2. group the selected students by city
3. calculate the total marks obtained by students in each city
4. sort the result in dec order of total marks. 
5. display only the city name and total marks.

db.studentdata.aggregate([{$match:{marks:{$gte:80}}},
    {$group:{_id:"$city",totalmarks:{$sum:"$marks"}}},
    {$sort:{totalmarks:-1}},{$project:{totalmarks:1,city:"$id"}}])